# Cloud Device Lab - Frontend Environment Variables
# ===================================================

# API BASE URL CONFIGURATION (CRITICAL FOR VERCEL)
# =================================================
# How it works:
# 1. If VITE_API_URL is set, use it (takes precedence)
# 2. If VITE_API_BASE_URL is set, use it
# 3. Otherwise, default to "/api" (relative to frontend)
#
# For LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
# Set to your local backend server (usually http://localhost:5000)
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api

# For VERCEL PRODUCTION (external backend):
# Required if backend is deployed separately from frontend.
# Get this URL from your backend service provider (Railway, Render, AWS EC2, etc.)
# 
# Examples:
# - Railway: https://your-app-production.up.railway.app/api
# - Render: https://your-api-server.onrender.com/api
# - AWS EC2: https://api.yourdomain.com/api
#
# IMPORTANT: If backend is NOT deployed or API is not configured on Vercel,
# device launches will fail with "Backend service unreachable" error.
#
# VITE_API_URL=https://your-api-server.railway.app/api

# Optional: Use this if you prefer to set just the base URL without /api
# (the system will automatically add /api suffix)
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5000

# WebSocket/Signaling Server (for WebRTC streaming)
# Optional for local development, recommended for production
VITE_SIGNALING_URL=http://localhost:5001

# WebRTC STUN Server (for NAT traversal)
# Default Google STUN server works for most cases
VITE_STUN_SERVER=stun:stun.l.google.com:19302

# Optional TURN servers for advanced NAT scenarios
# Uncomment and configure if users are behind restrictive firewalls
# VITE_TURN_SERVER=turn:turn.example.com:3478
# VITE_TURN_USERNAME=username
# VITE_TURN_PASSWORD=password

# Feature Flags
VITE_ENABLE_ANALYTICS=false
VITE_ENABLE_DEBUG=true

# Session Configuration
VITE_MAX_SESSION_DURATION=7200
VITE_SESSION_WARNING_TIME=300

# === LEGACY/OPTIONAL SANDBOX SETTINGS ===
# (These endpoints are handled by the unified API configuration above)
# Kept for backward compatibility only
VITE_SANDBOX_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api/sandbox
VITE_SANDBOX_POLL_INTERVAL=15000
VITE_SANDBOX_MAX_WAIT=300000

# =============================================
# VERCEL DEPLOYMENT INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================
#
# 1. In Vercel Dashboard, go to Settings → Environment Variables
#
# 2. Set VITE_API_URL to your backend service URL:
#    
#    VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend-domain.com/api
#    
#    You can get this URL from:
#    - Railway: https://dashboard.railway.app → Project → Settings → Deploy
#    - Render: https://dashboard.render.com → Service → Environment
#    - AWS: Your EC2 instance public IP or domain
#
# 3. If you haven't deployed a backend yet:
#    - The app will show "Backend service unreachable" on device launch
#    - First deploy your backend following backend/README.md
#    - Then add VITE_API_URL to Vercel environment variables
#
# 4. Redeploy frontend in Vercel after adding environment variables:
#    - Vercel → Project → Deployments → Redeploy
#    - Or push new commit to trigger automatic redeploy
#
# 5. Test the connection:
#    - Open deployed Vercel app in browser
#    - Try to launch Android or Windows device
#    - Check browser console (F12) for API logs if you set VITE_ENABLE_DEBUG=true
# =============================================

